07:01:16.000 --> 07:01:17.430
let me give a quick summary of the

07:01:17.440 --> 07:01:20.150
algorithm as we have it today as we've

07:01:20.160 --> 07:01:23.030
made a whole bunch of good progress. Um,

07:01:23.040 --> 07:01:25.350
the current algorithm works like this.

07:01:25.360 --> 07:01:27.830
You have a state buffer. It contains

07:01:27.840 --> 07:01:30.628
several trajectory segments.

07:01:30.638 --> 07:01:36.628
When you uh finish segments in training,

07:01:36.638 --> 07:01:40.708
you store the top k highest scoring

07:01:40.718 --> 07:01:45.030
segments according to summed to reward.

07:01:45.040 --> 07:01:46.708
You store the states associated with

07:01:46.718 --> 07:01:49.590
those segments into the buffer.

07:01:49.600 --> 07:01:51.670
Those cannot those segments in the

07:01:51.680 --> 07:01:54.230
buffer cannot get overwritten by other

07:01:54.240 --> 07:01:57.110
uh other segments from the buffer. Uh

07:01:57.120 --> 07:01:58.948
what it means by this is when you sample

07:01:58.958 --> 07:02:00.628
when you sample starting states from the

07:02:00.638 --> 07:02:02.310
buffer

07:02:02.320 --> 07:02:05.030
you cannot overwrite other segments that

07:02:05.040 --> 07:02:07.270
are in the buffer already with them.

07:02:07.280 --> 07:02:09.750
However, if you sample a starting state

07:02:09.760 --> 07:02:12.390
and you come up with a higher discounted

07:02:12.400 --> 07:02:14.150
return

07:02:14.160 --> 07:02:15.990
solve from wherever you start to the

07:02:16.000 --> 07:02:20.390
tail of the segment that can get added.

07:02:20.400 --> 07:02:23.030
So essentially this allows you to find a

07:02:23.040 --> 07:02:26.868
higher scoring or shorter solves

07:02:26.878 --> 07:02:31.190
from the state that you added.

07:02:32.948 --> 07:02:32.958
I think that this is fairly general

07:02:32.958 --> 07:02:35.270
because this is iterative improvement on

07:02:35.280 --> 07:02:38.788
a given trajectory.

07:02:38.798 --> 07:02:40.468
I think that is fine. I think that the

07:02:40.478 --> 07:02:43.910
chunk that is still not general is

07:02:43.920 --> 07:02:46.628
adding st adding segments to the buffer

07:02:46.638 --> 07:02:49.590
based on score

07:02:49.600 --> 07:02:51.990
because different episodes are not going

07:02:52.000 --> 07:02:55.030
to be necessarily the same score norm.

07:02:55.040 --> 07:02:56.708
